Hmm, maybe that will be the same day they implement proper Hide/Sneak for Wood Elf Rangers? =)  <br>
<br>
I used those skills once inside Crushbone sometime around level 10 (to CR my group) and beyond that the only time I use sneak is to buy from vendors that usually won't like me; and my hiding skills don't work all that well anymore - then again, having skills that capped at 75 will do that for you.<br>
<br>
It's purely down to Tracking being one of those &quot;class defining&quot; abilities; much in the same way as Backstab or Feign Death, for instance - which is why even though Bards and Druids get this ability, Rangers get the highest cap and practical &quot;track radius&quot;.<br>
<br>
Also, unless you're going the PvP route, Rogues don't usually hunt victims - they hunt money, ala the archetypal thief from D&amp;D - and the best places to do this aren't in the wilderness; they are in city or dungeon areas.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps. =)<br>
