>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/02 8:05:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23090.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tracking</span><hr size=1> In my opinion, rogues should at least be able to track humanoid mobs(ones that they can pickpocket).  I also think beastlords should be able to at least track animals.  This would solve all the problems with evil races not having trackers and would not overpower the classes or even make them comparable to rangers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukenwoodx2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kenwoodx2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/02 10:01:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23090.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.swbell.net/kenwoodx/images/greenguy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tracking</span><hr size=1> Well in a limited sense, the spells sense animals and sense undead work as a form of tracking.. I suppose they could give a sense humanoid skill to rogues.. <br>
<br>
I can see where everyone might like to have a tracking ability and certainly rogues have a pretty good reasoning as to why they would have that skill, but I think that most of the characters in fantasy that you can think of with this skill are either of the rangerish/warden type or are a mixture of several classes (maybe both rogue and ranger in the skills they possess)..  <br>
<br>
I think if you view a rogue as a thief then you've pretty much got all the skills a thief would have.  Thieves don't normally wander around chasing after people..  Normally they lie in wait until an unsuspecting victim wanders by..  With the hide/sneak skills and the ability to backstab I think they've pretty much nailed down the thief abilities of the rogue.  And we do have the illusion masks to at least simulate in some way the ability to assume other identities.<br>
<br>
Then you have evade, pick pocket, pick locks, and the other abilities that are pretty much exclusives of the rogue (with the exception of the few skills that bards share with us)..  All in all I think they've done a pretty good job with the skills that rogues have..  We are a unique class that requires a certain amount of intelligence to play.<br>
<br>
